1957;;Just My Luck;;British;;John Paddy Carstairs;;Norman Wisdom, Jill Dixon;;sports/comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_My_Luck_(1957_film);;Norman Hackett (Norman Wisdom) is employed in a jeweller's workshop and is innocently preoccupied with dreaming of meeting the window dresser in the shop across the street from his workplace. He wishes to purchase a diamond pendant for her and, after persuasion, gambles a pound on a six-horse accumulator at the Goodwood races. The bookmaker grows concerned when it appears Hackett, after winning on the first five races, could win over Â£16,000.